# Input
```css
/* should generate diagnostics */

/* 1. Basic duplicate: same selector twice in the same file */
.foo {}
.foo {}

/* 2. Duplicate type selector */
div { color: red; }
div { color: blue; }

/* 3. Duplicate inside same @media block */
@media (min-width: 600px) {
  .bar {}
  .bar {}
}

/* 4. Selector list: same list in different order counts as duplicate */
.a, .b {}
.b, .a {}

/* 5. Nesting resolved: `a { & b {} }` produces `a b`, same as explicit `a b {}` */
a b {}
a {
  & b {}
}

/* 6. Compound selector ordering: .a.b == .b.a */
.a.b {}
.b.a {}

/* 7. Type selector case-insensitivity: DIV == div */
DIV { color: red; }
div { color: blue; }

/* 8. Descendant via nesting: `.nav .link {}` == `.nav { .link {} }` */
.nav .link {}
.nav {
  .link {}
}

/* 9. Multi-level nesting: `.x .y .z {}` == `.x { .y { .z {} } }` */
.x .y .z {}
.x {
  .y {
    .z {}
  }
}

/* 10. Nesting with ampersand and pseudo-class:
   `button:hover {}` == `button { &:hover {} }` */
button:hover {}
button {
  &:hover {}
}

/* 11. Nesting with ampersand and pseudo-element:
   `span::before {}` == `span { &::before {} }` */
span::before {}
span {
  &::before {}
}

/* 12. Selector list duplicate via nesting: `.p .r, .q .r` == `.p, .q { .r {} }` */
.p .r {}
.q .r {}
.p, .q {
  .r {}
}

/* 13. Sibling combinator via nesting: `h3 ~ p {}` == `h3 { & ~ p {} }` */
h3 ~ p {}
h3 {
  & ~ p {}
}

/* 14. Duplicate with attribute selector */
[type="text"] {}
[type="text"] {}

/* 15. Duplicate with ID and class compound selector */
#main .content {}
#main {
  .content {}
}

```

